ipax-tools
==========

This repository contains code derived from third-party sources listed
below, alongside original tooling built on top of them.

1. IPAX 2 — Santiago Bustelo
   Website : https://www.bustelo.com.ar/
   Source  : https://icograma.com/index.php
   Status  : Permission granted 2026-06-10 — CC-BY attribution terms

   The IPAX scoring engine, ergonomics model, and perceptual dictionary
   in packages/core/src/ are derived from Santiago Bustelo's IPAX 2.
   See packages/core/NOTICE for the per-file breakdown.

   vendor/ contains unmodified snapshots of vendor engine drops, kept
   for diffing purposes when porting updates into packages/core — see
   packages/core/README.md for that workflow.

2. APCA W3 — Andrew Somers / Myndex Research
   Repository : https://github.com/Myndex/apca-w3
   Copyright  : © 2019-2022 Andrew Somers. All Rights Reserved.
   License    : W3 LICENSE (web content accessibility use)

   Reproduced unmodified as packages/core/src/apca-w3.js. Used for
   predicting perceptual contrast for web content per WCAG guidelines.
   The W3 license permits royalty-free use for this purpose. Prohibited
   uses include medical, clinical, aerospace, transportation, military,
   and applications not specific to web content.

Original work in this repository
